What is the smallest positive integer that ends in 9 and is divisible by 7?

9 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 19.

19 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 29.

29 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 39.

39 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 49.

49 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 59.

59 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 69.

69 is not divisible by 7, so we add 10 to get 79.

79 is divisible by 7, so the answer is $\boxed{79}$.
Final Answer: \boxed{$79$}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: We can start from 9 and keeping adding 10 until we reach an integer divisible by 7. It turns out that 9, 19, 29, and 39 are all not divisible by 7, but 49 is divisible by 7. Therefore, $\boxed{49}$ is the smallest integer that ends in a 9 and is divisible by 7.
